__SqlaTable__.sql:
select f.user_id, f.time 
from 
simulator_20220620.feed_actions f
left join 
simulator_20220620.message_actions m
on f.user_id = m.user_id
where m.user_id = 0

SELECT user_id, toDate(time) as time, count(user_id) as number_of_actions
from simulator_20220620.message_actions
group by user_id, time

select user_id, min(time) as start_date
from simulator_20220620.message_actions
group by user_id

select f.day as day, f.user_id as feed_users, m.user_id as message_users
from (
select count(DISTINCT user_id) as user_id, toDate(time) as day 
from simulator_20220620.feed_actions
group by day
) f
join (
select count(DISTINCT user_id) as user_id, toDate(time) as day 
from simulator_20220620.message_actions
group by day
) m
on f.day = m.day

select *
from 
(select * from simulator_20220620.feed_actions) fa
join 
(select * from simulator_20220620.message_actions) ma 
on fa.user_id = ma.user_id

select user_id, min(time) as start_date
from simulator_20220620.feed_actions
group by user_id

__SqlaTable__.sql:
select m.user_id, m.time 
from 
simulator_20220620.feed_actions f
right join 
simulator_20220620.message_actions m
on f.user_id = m.user_id and toStartOfDay(m.time) = toStartOfDay(f.time)
where f.user_id = 0
